1
00:02:43,480 --> 00:02:46,320
My daughter's birthday was ruined.
I can't let this go.

2
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:51,160
- How dare you ruin Ms. Mika's birthday?
- Dad?

3
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,440
Mr. Trai.

4
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:56,880
Why don't you die then?!
So Dad will have only me.

5
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:59,680
Do it. Kill me! Kill me!

6
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:03,120
They're suing us
for 20 million baht in damages.

7
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:04,400
20 million baht?

8
00:03:04,480 --> 00:03:07,200
People like you have ruined
so many bosses already, you know.

9
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:09,400
<i>You're picking a fight with my mom?</i>

10
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:11,520
<i>I'm gonna use the media to…</i>

11
00:03:12,760 --> 00:03:15,560
<i>From now on, it's just friendship.</i>

12
00:03:15,640 --> 00:03:18,000
<i>Heart for heart. Nothing owed.</i>

13
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:19,160
Did you find him?

14
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:25,560
You're still funny as always.

15
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:27,120
What do you want?

16
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:28,880
You really don't remember me?

17
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:34,520
Where are you going?!

18
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:37,360
You!

19
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,120
- Pakbung?
- Mr. Trai?

20
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:50,840
- What are you doing here?
- You're with Darin?

21
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:53,720
It's not family time now. We need to run.

22
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:56,920
What are you doing to my friend?

23
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,320
I need to talk to Pakbung.

24
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:00,760
Did Dad send you?

25
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:01,800
It has nothing to do with you.

26
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:03,160
Why not? She's my friend.

27
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:04,240
Since when did she become your friend?

28
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:06,800
- That's none of your business. It's mine.
- Hey!

29
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:08,080
5,000 an hour!

30
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:09,160
Whoever wants me,

31
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:10,440
pay up!

32
00:04:12,640 --> 00:04:15,360
- Pakbung! You monster!
- No one? Then every man for himself.

33
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:16,480
Give me my sister's money!

34
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:18,560
He's so damn persistent.

35
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:21,320
Die now!

36
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:33,000
Pakbung!

37
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:42,480
Help! He's on drugs. Help.

38
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:44,920
- Help. Grab him. He's on drugs.
- Let go of me!

39
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:47,920
- Catch him. Pakbung, are you okay?
- I'm okay.

40
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,120
Give me my sister's money!

41
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:52,200
Hey! Don't touch me! Let go! Pakbung!

42
00:04:52,280 --> 00:04:53,800
Hey, I said let go!

43
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:55,120
- You okay?
- Take him to the police.

44
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,040
- I'm okay.
- Noy!

45
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:57,800
- Follow me.
- Pakbung!

46
00:04:57,880 --> 00:04:59,920
- Give me my sister's money!
- Follow me. This way.

47
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,960
Don't let him go!

48
00:05:04,880 --> 00:05:05,880
Does it hurt, Trai?

49
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,160
Hey.

50
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:10,160
Go clean the wound first.

51
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:12,280
Who knows what that knife's been through.

52
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:17,040
Is there a clinic or pharmacy around here?
I'll go buy some medicine.

53
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:19,120
Stop acting tough.
You're hurt too, aren't you?

54
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:22,160
- I'm fine.
- Why are you so stubborn?

55
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:23,440
Huh?

56
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:25,920
Does it hurt?

57
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:29,800
You're dripping blood, and you're still
worried about someone else.

58
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:30,880
You never learn.

59
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:37,640
I brought her here.
Am I supposed to just not care?

60
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:40,160
You knew what my neighborhood's like.

61
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:42,320
Why bring her here in the first place?

62
00:05:48,960 --> 00:05:51,040
I told you I'm really fine.

63
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:54,840
You stay here with Pakbung.
I'll go buy some medicine.

64
00:05:58,680 --> 00:05:59,560
- Ow!
- Da!

65
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:05,960
- I said don't act tough. Walk slowly.
- Mr. Trai.

66
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,480
Mr. Trai, you're injured?

67
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:11,000
If Mr. Tritot finds out, I'm dead.

68
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:12,640
- Let's go to the hospital.
- It's nothing.

69
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:14,320
Help Da.

70
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:19,920
Walk slowly.

71
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:07,680
Back to the office.

72
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:10,480
Wait.

73
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:17,240
You dropped this.

74
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:24,360
What time will you arrive, Dad?

75
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:28,840
Trai caused trouble again?

76
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:31,920
So you have to go fix it again, right?

77
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:35,400
It's okay, Dad. I understand.

78
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:38,080
We can celebrate later…

79
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:49,760
Watch out! The cart has no brakes!

80
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:01,720
I'm so sorry.

81
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,320
‪Wash your face too.

82
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:24,000
Okay. That's enough.

83
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:25,680
‪Alright.

84
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:30,080
- Let me wipe you down a bit.
- It's okay.

85
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:38,080
I'm really, really sorry.

86
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,120
You're soaked.

87
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:46,120
But at least

88
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:48,080
this didn't get wet.

89
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:58,200
It's just a piece of paper.

90
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:04,320
First-class honors?

91
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:07,680
Can I see it?

92
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,040
Here.

93
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:16,160
That's amazing!

94
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:18,680
You're incredible!

95
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:26,320
It's just first-class honors.

96
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:30,120
Are you a gift from the gods or something?

97
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:32,040
How can you be this handsome

98
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,440
and this smart?

99
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:37,640
A gift from the gods? You're exaggerating.

100
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:41,680
So…

101
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:42,880
are those for sale?

102
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,400
These?

103
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:49,440
No.

104
00:09:50,040 --> 00:09:52,080
I rent them out as photo props.

105
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:08,520
If you don't mind,

106
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:11,000
may I give you flowers?

107
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:12,520
This one's

108
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:14,520
an apology.

109
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:27,320
And this one, congratulations

110
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:29,800
on achieving first-class honors.

111
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:33,160
Honestly, I've never met
someone like this in real life.

112
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:35,160
You're the first.

113
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:38,320
I wish you success in life

114
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:40,400
and

115
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:42,920
lots of happiness.

116
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:47,960
Mr. First-Class Honors?

117
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:49,800
Why didn't you say so from the start?

118
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,920
You remembered me
because of the handkerchief?

119
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,200
Well,

120
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:57,600
my memory isn't as perfect as someone
who graduated with first-class honors.

121
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:03,400
I embroidered this myself.

122
00:11:08,560 --> 00:11:09,840
So,

123
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:12,720
you're here just to return this to me?

124
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:15,320
You gave it to me, didn't you?

125
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:22,960
You didn't come to charge me
for dry-cleaning that day, did you?

126
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:24,720
If I did, would you pay me?

127
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:27,000
- How much are you asking?
- How much can you pay?

128
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:31,880
Well…

129
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:36,240
The same price
as the handkerchief in your hand.

130
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:37,640
We're even.

131
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:41,320
Then I guess I owe you.

132
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:53,200
Owe what?

133
00:12:09,360 --> 00:12:11,800
Did you approach that girl
because of Mr. Trai?

134
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:13,880
Why would you think that?

135
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:17,280
I saw that Mr. Trai is close to her,

136
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:19,920
so I thought
you might have some kind of plan.

137
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:21,840
I'm not like my dad.

138
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:24,800
I'll never sacrifice myself for Trai.

139
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:27,680
Right.

140
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:29,720
Then, does that mean

141
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:31,920
you really like that girl?

142
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:48,880
You were going to see your friend,

143
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:50,800
but you two didn't even get to talk.

144
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:53,400
It's all because of me.

145
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:56,560
It's not because of you.
You're not that important.

146
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:06,240
Go help Da.

147
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:07,880
Well,

148
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:09,600
you're not going to run away, right?

149
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:11,280
Say you won't run away.

150
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,440
It hurts that badly?

151
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,000
Mr. Trai.

152
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,240
You ungrateful son.

153
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:37,040
Do you not care at all
that Darin is my wife?

154
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:41,120
Mr. Tritot.

155
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:43,240
Trai didn't do anything.

156
00:13:44,160 --> 00:13:45,600
You're disgusting.

157
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:48,400
You're more shameless than I ever thought.

158
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:52,360
And you stoop lower
than I ever thought you could.

159
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:56,560
You've already thought
that I've slept with Da.

160
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:58,440
Then let it be that way.

161
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:02,600
I took her to a hotel.

162
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:06,400
- It was so damn good.
- Trai!

163
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,200
You ungrateful bastard.

164
00:14:08,280 --> 00:14:10,480
Have you ever made me happy even once?

165
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:12,440
And have you ever made me happy?

166
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:15,560
Instead of asking what happened,

167
00:14:15,640 --> 00:14:18,960
you judge everything on your own.
For you, I've never done anything good.

168
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:22,800
I'm wrong. I'm bad.

169
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:24,440
I'm trash.

170
00:14:25,920 --> 00:14:29,480
So why should I even explain
when my words never enter your head?

171
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:31,960
- Because you're rotten!
- Fine. I'm rotten!

172
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:34,200
Then can you stop
interfering with my life?

173
00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:36,360
Trai! Trai!

174
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:38,000
Trai! Trai!

175
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:39,520
- Trai!
- Mr. Trai.

176
00:14:45,640 --> 00:14:46,520
This is why.

177
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:49,080
I don't let you go

178
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:50,680
because you refuse to grow up.

179
00:14:51,280 --> 00:14:52,400
I refuse to grow up?

180
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:53,800
How exactly do I refuse to grow up?

181
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:56,720
You're childish.
Your thinking is childish.

182
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:57,800
Do you know

183
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,280
what you did this morning?

184
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:03,440
You cost me an investor.

185
00:15:07,640 --> 00:15:09,840
So you're angry because of money?

186
00:15:11,720 --> 00:15:14,680
Your life is nothing
but money, money, money.

187
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:16,160
- How greedy can you be?!
- Yes!

188
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:19,240
Because I can't just
conjure money out of thin air.

189
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:20,760
Trai.

190
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:22,680
I'll tell you what.

191
00:15:24,040 --> 00:15:25,520
Life isn't as easy as you think.

192
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:29,320
Happiness doesn't just fall into your lap.

193
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:30,520
Try it.

194
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:33,000
Try going without food
for three or four days.

195
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:35,640
Try being sick and dying
without money for treatment.

196
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:38,680
Try being looked down on like a stray dog.

197
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:40,240
Does it have to get that bad

198
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:43,840
before you finally understand
who I've been doing all this for?

199
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:45,640
It's not for me, at least.

200
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:46,800
Trai!

201
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:50,680
Do you have any idea
how much capital Dad's business requires?

202
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:52,800
You've never helped him. You have no idea

203
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:55,480
how hard he's worked
to get where we are today.

204
00:15:57,440 --> 00:15:59,000
And after all that struggle,

205
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:01,680
you have money and everything you want.

206
00:16:02,280 --> 00:16:03,400
Let me ask you something.

207
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:05,840
Are you really happy?

208
00:16:07,640 --> 00:16:10,960
Have you ever looked at yourself
in the mirror? Who you are now

209
00:16:11,040 --> 00:16:14,120
is nowhere near a happy person.
Not even close.

210
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:15,560
And who?

211
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:17,560
Who is it that made me unhappy?

212
00:16:18,320 --> 00:16:19,280
Do you know?!

213
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:21,480
Then why keep me by your side?

214
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:23,200
Let me go. Let me go.

215
00:16:24,240 --> 00:16:26,920
If being close only makes us miserable,

216
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:29,280
if being close
only makes us hate each other more,

217
00:16:30,040 --> 00:16:31,120
then let me go.

218
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:36,360
Let me live my own life. Don't make me
hate you more than I already do!

219
00:16:46,520 --> 00:16:48,240
You really hate me that much, Trai?

220
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:50,960
You really hate me, Trai?

221
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:52,400
Yes.

222
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:56,200
I… hate… you.

223
00:17:05,839 --> 00:17:07,040
Then go.

224
00:17:08,640 --> 00:17:09,440
Go.

225
00:17:10,119 --> 00:17:12,200
Go live the life you want

226
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:14,160
without my money.

227
00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:15,839
I want to see

228
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:18,680
whether you'll be happy
the way you think you will.

229
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:22,599
Go!

230
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:24,079
Go now!

231
00:17:26,599 --> 00:17:28,840
This must be the first decision

232
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:31,760
you've ever made for my sake.

233
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:33,360
Thank you.

234
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:37,000
Don't follow him.

235
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:41,360
Let him go.

236
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:43,320
Let him go die wherever he wants.

237
00:17:56,520 --> 00:17:57,840
Should I call the doctor?

238
00:17:58,880 --> 00:18:00,320
No need.

239
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:03,080
Dad, but you're still not okay.

240
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:06,200
I want to be alone.

241
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:08,000
Dad…

242
00:18:09,360 --> 00:18:10,200
Get out.

243
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:12,920
Yes.

244
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:46,960
Trai made Dad cry. You bastard…

245
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:51,400
Mr. Trai needs to be taught a lesson.

246
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:06,720
You think
I can't survive without you, Dad?

247
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:11,880
I'll show you I can be happy

248
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:13,240
even without your money.

249
00:19:28,840 --> 00:19:30,360
Did Dad send people after me?

250
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:43,160
Samlee?

251
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:45,160
Pakbung?

252
00:20:00,720 --> 00:20:03,480
I don't know
how Mr. Lee got Samlee's number,

253
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:07,000
but he called to ask
if you were at my place.

254
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:10,840
So I guessed you were in trouble

255
00:20:10,920 --> 00:20:13,520
and that you might be hiding here.

256
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:19,880
Pakbung was worried about you so, so much,

257
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:22,160
so she dragged me here to check on you.

258
00:20:26,080 --> 00:20:28,320
Friends worry about each other.

259
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:32,160
Thanks.

260
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:36,160
You fought with your dad again?

261
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:42,200
This time was probably the last time.

262
00:20:43,840 --> 00:20:45,240
He set me free.

263
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:00,920
Anything you wanna get off your chest?

264
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:16,360
Yeah, I know.

265
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:23,880
Are you okay?

266
00:21:25,360 --> 00:21:26,720
I understand you now,

267
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:30,280
what it felt like
when your dad slapped you.

268
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:32,720
It's not my face that hurts.

269
00:21:34,240 --> 00:21:35,560
It's my heart.

270
00:21:36,160 --> 00:21:37,400
Does it hurt a lot?

271
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:40,520
Why can't we ever talk nicely?

272
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:44,920
I never wanted to fight with him,

273
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:48,520
but every time we see each other,
we just blow up at each other.

274
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:50,320
Now,

275
00:21:50,840 --> 00:21:52,480
it's like we've become enemies.

276
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,400
I don't hate him.

277
00:21:56,520 --> 00:21:57,680
I don't want to hate him.

278
00:21:58,440 --> 00:22:00,240
But does being a family

279
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:03,760
have to hurt this much?

280
00:22:05,800 --> 00:22:07,600
Maybe because it's family,

281
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:10,880
that's why it can hurt this much.

282
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:31,800
What did I do wrong, Dao?

283
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:34,440
What did I do wrong?

284
00:22:36,840 --> 00:22:38,800
Why does Trai never understand me?

285
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,600
If you were still here…

286
00:22:56,880 --> 00:22:59,160
he wouldn't hate me, right?

287
00:23:35,160 --> 00:23:36,040
Why are you here?

288
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:37,800
Who allowed you to come in?

289
00:23:38,640 --> 00:23:40,120
You misunderstood Trai.

290
00:23:40,840 --> 00:23:43,640
- How?
- Trai and I didn't sleep together.

291
00:23:43,720 --> 00:23:45,360
Trai was attacked by a guy high on drugs,

292
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:48,920
so we went to the hospital.
If you don't believe me, ask Lee.

293
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:52,320
- Then why are you only telling me now?
- You didn't ask.

294
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:55,840
Just like Trai said,

295
00:23:57,560 --> 00:24:00,200
you judge everything
through your own filthy assumptions.

296
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:06,320
Honestly, I also want Trai
to be free from a father like you.

297
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:12,480
But you should know this.

298
00:24:13,640 --> 00:24:15,400
If anything happens to Trai,

299
00:24:16,480 --> 00:24:18,440
it'll be all your fault.

300
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:42,600
How's the wound on your arm?

301
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:46,120
Hey, don't talk about it.

302
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:47,920
The second you mention it, it hurts.

303
00:24:53,320 --> 00:24:54,240
Anyway,

304
00:24:54,320 --> 00:24:56,120
why did Rachen come see you?

305
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:04,560
And why did you bring your ex to my place?

306
00:25:05,560 --> 00:25:07,320
I didn't bring her.

307
00:25:07,400 --> 00:25:09,760
It was her car, and she was already in it.

308
00:25:10,720 --> 00:25:13,440
Hold on.
I asked first, so you answer first.

309
00:25:18,800 --> 00:25:20,360
Mr. Rachen's flirting with me.

310
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:22,360
Huh?

311
00:25:23,160 --> 00:25:24,840
We've met before,

312
00:25:25,360 --> 00:25:26,800
and he remembered me.

313
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:30,640
He even kept the handkerchief I gave him.

314
00:25:31,240 --> 00:25:33,000
Pakbung, can you not daydream?

315
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:35,200
Rachen? Liking you?

316
00:25:40,480 --> 00:25:41,440
Why?

317
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:43,760
With a face like this,

318
00:25:43,840 --> 00:25:45,560
can't I have someone who likes me?

319
00:25:50,120 --> 00:25:52,400
Or do I have to be pretty

320
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:54,920
like Ms. Darin

321
00:25:55,520 --> 00:25:58,640
for someone to fall
head over heels for me?

322
00:25:59,360 --> 00:26:01,120
I didn't mean that.

323
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:03,240
Rachen hates me.

324
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:05,600
He wants to kill me, Pakbung.

325
00:26:05,680 --> 00:26:12,320
The chance he's being sincere with you
is less than 0.00000001 percent.

326
00:26:14,920 --> 00:26:17,000
He offered to buy me a new phone.

327
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:18,920
Huh?

328
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:20,360
He asked for my number,

329
00:26:20,440 --> 00:26:22,920
but my phone got stolen.

330
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:26,280
So he wanted to buy me a new one.

331
00:26:26,880 --> 00:26:28,920
Did he pick up Dad's habit,

332
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:30,640
always winning people over with money?

333
00:26:31,240 --> 00:26:33,120
If you don’t want him
to win me over with money,

334
00:26:33,720 --> 00:26:35,240
then you do it first.

335
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:38,160
Buy me a new phone.

336
00:26:43,480 --> 00:26:45,600
- You cheapskate.
- Ow.

337
00:26:49,120 --> 00:26:50,000
What?

338
00:26:50,080 --> 00:26:51,880
Hey, go hide. Move.

339
00:26:59,400 --> 00:27:00,440
Was that a gunshot?

340
00:29:44,080 --> 00:29:46,880
Hey! Hey!

341
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:51,040
Huh?

342
00:29:51,560 --> 00:29:52,680
Pakbung.

343
00:29:55,280 --> 00:29:56,320
Hey.

344
00:29:57,080 --> 00:29:59,280
- Hey.
- What?

345
00:30:01,880 --> 00:30:03,480
Hey. Mr. Trai!

346
00:30:03,560 --> 00:30:05,200
Mr. Trai! Mr. Trai!

347
00:30:05,280 --> 00:30:06,520
Mr. Trai! Ah!

348
00:30:06,600 --> 00:30:09,800
Hold on. Here.

349
00:30:09,880 --> 00:30:11,800
- Mr. Trai!
- Use this.

350
00:30:12,440 --> 00:30:14,040
Hey!

351
00:30:14,120 --> 00:30:16,440
Mr. Trai! Mr. Trai!

352
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:18,560
Wake up! Wake up!

353
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:20,480
Hey, wake up!

354
00:30:23,600 --> 00:30:24,560
Hey.

355
00:30:26,080 --> 00:30:26,920
Pakbung.

356
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:27,960
Are you okay?

357
00:30:28,040 --> 00:30:30,360
I'm okay. I'm not dead yet.

358
00:30:31,120 --> 00:30:33,320
Idiot. Don't say that.

359
00:30:49,080 --> 00:30:50,200
Move aside.

360
00:31:10,440 --> 00:31:12,440
Hey! Mr. Trai!

361
00:31:13,520 --> 00:31:14,520
Mr. Trai!

362
00:31:32,280 --> 00:31:34,320
Trai is my son. Which room is he in?

363
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:36,800
One moment, please. I'll check for you.

364
00:31:36,880 --> 00:31:38,520
TREATMENT ROOM 1

365
00:31:46,880 --> 00:31:47,720
Trai?

366
00:31:51,480 --> 00:31:52,400
Trai.

367
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:28,520
- Trai. Trai…
- Dad?

368
00:32:30,120 --> 00:32:31,040
Trai.

369
00:32:43,560 --> 00:32:44,560
You're okay, right?

370
00:32:47,960 --> 00:32:49,240
It hurts.

371
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:54,840
Dad…

372
00:32:58,880 --> 00:33:01,440
Please be okay. I'm glad you're okay.

373
00:33:46,040 --> 00:33:47,760
Last night wasn't a dream, was it?

374
00:33:49,080 --> 00:33:50,040
What dream?

375
00:33:51,800 --> 00:33:52,880
That you hugged me?

376
00:33:56,000 --> 00:33:59,160
Why? I can't hug my own son now?

377
00:34:07,880 --> 00:34:08,800
Are you okay?

378
00:34:10,239 --> 00:34:11,920
You don't really want to hug…

379
00:34:12,920 --> 00:34:14,760
the person you want dead, right?

380
00:34:22,080 --> 00:34:25,120
- You didn't mean…
- Since I came back to Thailand,

381
00:34:25,719 --> 00:34:27,760
I've been attacked twice.

382
00:34:28,440 --> 00:34:30,199
And both times,

383
00:34:31,679 --> 00:34:33,480
it was after you and I fought.

384
00:34:35,719 --> 00:34:36,560
Trai.

385
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:42,400
I stole your woman
because I wanted you to stop being stupid.

386
00:34:43,120 --> 00:34:46,280
I never thought of and will never think of
letting you die.

387
00:34:48,360 --> 00:34:50,199
Can I trust you?

388
00:34:56,560 --> 00:34:58,720
Even if I'm not the father you dreamed of,

389
00:35:05,080 --> 00:35:07,640
can you at least
take me off your suspect list?

390
00:35:12,760 --> 00:35:14,480
The police would like
to take Mr. Trai's statement.

391
00:35:15,160 --> 00:35:16,040
Alright.

392
00:35:24,480 --> 00:35:27,880
The police have checked
the CCTV around the scene,

393
00:35:28,560 --> 00:35:31,120
but they still don't have any lead
on Mr. Trai's attacker.

394
00:35:32,480 --> 00:35:33,800
Clean work.

395
00:35:34,960 --> 00:35:36,440
Too bad he was left alive.

396
00:35:58,760 --> 00:35:59,800
Here.

397
00:36:13,960 --> 00:36:16,800
Contact the best investigation team
you can find.

398
00:36:16,880 --> 00:36:18,080
Report directly to me.

399
00:36:18,160 --> 00:36:19,080
Yes, sir.

400
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:21,560
Install more CCTV at the house

401
00:36:21,640 --> 00:36:22,960
and at the school too.

402
00:36:23,480 --> 00:36:26,440
And get five plainclothes bodyguards

403
00:36:26,520 --> 00:36:27,360
to be with Trai.

404
00:36:27,960 --> 00:36:28,760
Yes, sir.

405
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:30,520
Whoa, Dad.

406
00:36:30,600 --> 00:36:32,920
Do I not look like a prisoner enough?

407
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:47,600
YOU DESERVE TO DIE, YOU PIECE OF SHIT

408
00:36:47,680 --> 00:36:49,520
I'LL KILL YOU

409
00:36:52,520 --> 00:36:54,680
TRAI, YOU'RE DEAD

410
00:36:57,680 --> 00:36:58,640
Who sent this, Dad?

411
00:36:59,520 --> 00:37:00,880
We're checking.

412
00:37:00,960 --> 00:37:03,920
Whoever sent it seems highly skilled,
leaving no traces at all.

413
00:37:05,760 --> 00:37:07,720
It has to be someone who hates me

414
00:37:08,920 --> 00:37:10,280
but is targeting you.

415
00:37:11,560 --> 00:37:14,280
Only a few people know my movements.

416
00:37:15,760 --> 00:37:18,120
Which means the person sending this

417
00:37:20,160 --> 00:37:21,880
is closer than we think.

418
00:37:25,600 --> 00:37:26,600
Who do you suspect?

419
00:37:36,760 --> 00:37:38,000
Speaking of the devil.

420
00:37:38,960 --> 00:37:40,920
- How are you?
- Still not dead.

421
00:37:41,920 --> 00:37:42,760
Disappointed?

422
00:37:44,800 --> 00:37:47,280
- Have we found the attacker, Dad?
- Not yet.

423
00:37:48,480 --> 00:37:49,440
But it's not hard to guess.

424
00:37:50,760 --> 00:37:52,480
You think I sent someone to kill you?

425
00:37:53,080 --> 00:37:54,440
It makes perfect sense.

426
00:37:56,120 --> 00:37:58,600
I'm just sick of you causing problems
for Dad all the time.

427
00:37:59,280 --> 00:38:01,200
But I've never thought of killing you.

428
00:38:01,280 --> 00:38:03,080
Then can I see your phone?

429
00:38:04,720 --> 00:38:07,400
Ah, I promise

430
00:38:08,400 --> 00:38:10,280
I won't open the porn
you've secretly saved.

431
00:38:12,720 --> 00:38:15,120
I just want to check your call log
and your messages.

432
00:38:16,160 --> 00:38:19,080
If I did it, I wouldn't be stupid enough
to keep evidence on my phone.

433
00:38:20,160 --> 00:38:22,480
So where would someone
smart like you keep it, then?

434
00:38:23,840 --> 00:38:25,000
I didn't do it.

435
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:28,080
And I don't need to prove anything to you.

436
00:38:30,440 --> 00:38:31,280
Scared, huh?

437
00:38:37,760 --> 00:38:38,920
Rachen.

438
00:38:40,280 --> 00:38:42,640
I know you'd never do that
to your own brother.

439
00:38:43,440 --> 00:38:44,800
I trust you.

440
00:38:45,520 --> 00:38:47,200
But for your brother to feel at ease,

441
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:49,680
it's just a phone, isn't it?

442
00:38:51,040 --> 00:38:52,560
You've got nothing to hide.

443
00:38:53,880 --> 00:38:54,880
Dad.

444
00:38:55,640 --> 00:38:59,240
If you trust me, you should explain
to Trai that I'm not the one who did it.

445
00:39:00,960 --> 00:39:02,240
Then…

446
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:05,400
Go ahead. Check it.

447
00:39:06,120 --> 00:39:08,200
See if I'm really trying to kill your son.

448
00:39:18,280 --> 00:39:19,400
Excuse me, Bro.

449
00:39:45,280 --> 00:39:47,240
It's because I'm not your real son, right?

450
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:49,240
That's why you don't trust me?

451
00:40:00,360 --> 00:40:01,200
Your tea, ma'am.

452
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:09,360
Be Rich stock is climbing
every single day,

453
00:40:09,440 --> 00:40:10,840
and the app hasn't even launched yet.

454
00:40:11,520 --> 00:40:12,960
It's launching next month, right?

455
00:40:13,600 --> 00:40:15,160
Once the app goes live,

456
00:40:15,800 --> 00:40:18,600
Be Rich will make a fortune.

457
00:40:18,680 --> 00:40:20,440
I think

458
00:40:20,520 --> 00:40:22,760
you should buy more shares in Be Rich.

459
00:40:22,840 --> 00:40:24,120
Don't tell me what to do.

460
00:40:25,480 --> 00:40:27,240
Uh, sorry, ma'am.

461
00:40:27,320 --> 00:40:28,400
I…

462
00:40:29,200 --> 00:40:30,160
I just

463
00:40:30,240 --> 00:40:32,600
want you to get what you deserve.

464
00:40:33,200 --> 00:40:36,120
And I think Be Rich could go even further

465
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:38,200
if it were in the hands
of a capable woman like you.

466
00:40:38,280 --> 00:40:40,440
I still can't interfere yet.

467
00:40:40,520 --> 00:40:41,760
Right now, Tritot

468
00:40:41,840 --> 00:40:44,080
and Trai are the major shareholders.

469
00:40:47,400 --> 00:40:48,960
Unless

470
00:40:50,360 --> 00:40:51,760
one of them…

471
00:40:53,200 --> 00:40:54,040
dies.

472
00:40:55,800 --> 00:40:58,240
Then taking over Be Rich
would become much easier.

473
00:41:02,560 --> 00:41:03,800
Mrs. Mookmanee.

474
00:41:20,360 --> 00:41:21,760
You managed to get the footage.

475
00:41:22,520 --> 00:41:24,080
You deserve to be Dad's right-hand man.

476
00:41:25,720 --> 00:41:27,920
I created a fake account
and posted the clip,

477
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:30,520
acting like a Good Samaritan nearby

478
00:41:30,600 --> 00:41:33,920
so it won't trace back to Pakbung,
just like you asked.

479
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:35,720
But if Mrs. Mookmanee sees it,

480
00:41:35,800 --> 00:41:38,480
this clip will be
on a countdown to getting deleted.

481
00:41:40,160 --> 00:41:42,280
Let them delete it.
We just need people to see it.

482
00:41:43,680 --> 00:41:45,480
The mother who worked her ass off
to protect her image

483
00:41:46,080 --> 00:41:47,680
which now gets wrecked
because of her daughter.

484
00:41:48,280 --> 00:41:49,720
I'd love to see what happens next.

485
00:41:49,800 --> 00:41:51,640
Didn't you say you wouldn't get involved?

486
00:41:52,240 --> 00:41:53,680
Hey, I'm not getting involved.

487
00:41:54,280 --> 00:41:55,480
I've got nothing to do with it.

488
00:41:56,680 --> 00:41:57,880
You guys are the ones who do.

489
00:41:57,960 --> 00:41:58,960
Sorry, Mr. Trai.

490
00:41:59,040 --> 00:42:00,520
I'm the one getting involved.

491
00:42:05,840 --> 00:42:06,680
You're getting involved…

492
00:42:21,960 --> 00:42:23,760
What's the matter, Mom?

493
00:42:24,360 --> 00:42:26,840
I'm tired.
I want to go upstairs and shower.

494
00:42:29,280 --> 00:42:30,320
You still don't get it?

495
00:42:32,920 --> 00:42:36,000
A Good Samaritan
saw what happened and posted it.

496
00:42:41,360 --> 00:42:44,160
The clip's filmed from far away.
You can't even tell it's me.

497
00:42:45,520 --> 00:42:47,080
And she came at you first, Mom,

498
00:42:47,160 --> 00:42:48,600
so I couldn't take it.

499
00:42:49,600 --> 00:42:51,480
And don't worry, okay?

500
00:42:55,640 --> 00:42:58,440
Because I took her phone with me.

501
00:42:59,040 --> 00:43:00,640
There's no evidence.

502
00:43:04,880 --> 00:43:06,560
Is that what I taught you?

503
00:43:11,480 --> 00:43:12,440
Mom.

504
00:43:13,040 --> 00:43:17,200
It's just like how you handled
those diamond dealers who cheated you.

505
00:43:19,640 --> 00:43:22,640
- Mom.
- When I go after someone,

506
00:43:22,720 --> 00:43:25,560
I make sure no one can come after me.

507
00:43:25,640 --> 00:43:29,840
Not showing your face, slapping them
like some uneducated street trash,

508
00:43:30,600 --> 00:43:32,520
why are you this stupid, huh?

509
00:43:32,600 --> 00:43:34,240
Mrs. Mook.

510
00:43:34,320 --> 00:43:36,640
Mrs. Mook, Ms. Mika can't breathe.

511
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:04,480
Why hasn't she come yet?

512
00:44:05,440 --> 00:44:06,800
She should've seen the clip by now.

513
00:44:13,960 --> 00:44:14,920
Who are you waiting for?

514
00:44:16,520 --> 00:44:17,560
No one.

515
00:44:18,280 --> 00:44:21,880
Um… I downloaded the app
and created an account for you already.

516
00:44:21,960 --> 00:44:22,840
Your new phone.

517
00:44:22,920 --> 00:44:24,880
Look. She's on live right now.

518
00:44:28,440 --> 00:44:29,280
What so funny?

519
00:44:29,360 --> 00:44:30,640
I want you to watch, Mr. Trai.

520
00:44:37,160 --> 00:44:38,320
Oh, right.

521
00:44:38,920 --> 00:44:39,920
Don't forget to watch it.

522
00:44:45,800 --> 00:44:47,480
<i>Here.</i>

523
00:44:47,560 --> 00:44:49,680
<i>It's done. The color is perfect.</i>

524
00:44:49,760 --> 00:44:51,520
<i>So on point.</i>

525
00:44:51,600 --> 00:44:53,840
Okay, so what now? What now?

526
00:44:53,920 --> 00:44:56,800
Let's see how long-lasting it is.

527
00:44:56,880 --> 00:44:58,360
Help me hold this. Yeah.

528
00:44:58,440 --> 00:44:59,800
- Okay.
- Alright, let's see.

529
00:44:59,880 --> 00:45:02,680
Here we go. Water here.

530
00:45:02,760 --> 00:45:04,600
- Wow.
- Here we go.

531
00:45:04,680 --> 00:45:06,840
There's water in my eyes,
but the brows are still here.

532
00:45:07,440 --> 00:45:09,080
No smudging, no peeling, no patchiness.

533
00:45:09,880 --> 00:45:11,680
Whether you're swinging your arms
on a beach walk

534
00:45:11,760 --> 00:45:13,760
or strolling the market with your lover,

535
00:45:13,840 --> 00:45:16,600
your brows will stay arched for wealth.

536
00:45:16,680 --> 00:45:17,960
If you're interested,

537
00:45:18,040 --> 00:45:20,200
tap Basket 3 to order now.

538
00:45:24,120 --> 00:45:24,960
Oh,

539
00:45:26,360 --> 00:45:29,120
so you didn't come visit
because you were busy live selling?

540
00:45:29,200 --> 00:45:31,280
Oh, hey.

541
00:45:31,360 --> 00:45:34,160
Mr. Trai is watching our livestream?

542
00:45:34,760 --> 00:45:36,400
- Where?
- Right here.

543
00:45:37,680 --> 00:45:40,360
<i>Hi, Mr. Trai.</i>

544
00:45:40,440 --> 00:45:41,280
Oh?

545
00:45:42,040 --> 00:45:43,000
Uh.

546
00:45:44,600 --> 00:45:46,040
Is it the same Trai?

547
00:45:46,880 --> 00:45:49,160
Please verify yourself.

548
00:45:49,240 --> 00:45:51,280
Normal Trai, press one.

549
00:45:52,200 --> 00:45:54,760
Billionaire Trai, press two.

550
00:45:56,640 --> 00:45:59,440
Billionaire Trai? Okay.

551
00:46:00,040 --> 00:46:01,200
Here.

552
00:46:02,320 --> 00:46:03,360
<i>It's really Mr. Trai.</i>

553
00:46:05,280 --> 00:46:07,760
If you can watch us,
that means you're better now, right?

554
00:46:07,840 --> 00:46:09,240
Better, my ass.

555
00:46:09,320 --> 00:46:10,480
Why didn't you come visit?

556
00:46:10,560 --> 00:46:12,240
If you're lonely at the hospital,

557
00:46:12,320 --> 00:46:14,400
do you want to buy eyebrow pencils

558
00:46:14,480 --> 00:46:16,640
to give to the nurses?

559
00:46:16,720 --> 00:46:19,200
If you're interested, tap Basket 3

560
00:46:19,280 --> 00:46:21,080
right now.

561
00:46:22,880 --> 00:46:24,120
If you buy out

562
00:46:24,200 --> 00:46:26,720
the whole basket,

563
00:46:26,800 --> 00:46:29,480
Pakbung will ship it for free,

564
00:46:29,560 --> 00:46:32,440
delivering straight to your heart.

565
00:46:34,840 --> 00:46:37,080
So you'll only show up
when I bait you with money?

566
00:46:39,200 --> 00:46:43,200
You stingy… cheapskate.

567
00:46:43,280 --> 00:46:44,720
CHEAPSKATE

568
00:46:44,800 --> 00:46:46,800
Yes, I'm cheap.

569
00:46:47,560 --> 00:46:49,600
But this problem can disappear immediately

570
00:46:49,680 --> 00:46:51,400
if you use this.

571
00:46:52,720 --> 00:46:55,080
Senna extract!

572
00:46:55,160 --> 00:46:56,680
Great detox.

573
00:46:56,760 --> 00:46:58,520
- Explosive…
- Bowels.

574
00:46:58,600 --> 00:47:00,280
- Flush out number two…
- Waste.

575
00:47:00,360 --> 00:47:02,360
- <i>Bestie for your…</i>
- <i>Bathroom.</i>

576
00:47:02,440 --> 00:47:06,120
Constipated, Mr. Trai?
Get this one. Tap Basket

577
00:47:06,200 --> 00:47:09,120
Number 8.

578
00:47:17,040 --> 00:47:19,320
So idiotic.

579
00:47:19,920 --> 00:47:21,480
Oh.

580
00:47:21,560 --> 00:47:23,560
Idiotic?

581
00:47:25,040 --> 00:47:26,800
How idiotic, mild or severe?

582
00:47:27,760 --> 00:47:29,120
If it's severe,

583
00:47:29,880 --> 00:47:31,560
you need this.

584
00:47:31,640 --> 00:47:34,560
Super ginkgo extract.

585
00:47:34,640 --> 00:47:37,720
Boost memory, sharpen thinking,
nourish your brain,

586
00:47:37,800 --> 00:47:39,720
<i>nourish your heart.</i>
<i>Your brain will be sharp.</i>

587
00:47:39,800 --> 00:47:42,640
This is FDA-approved too.

588
00:47:42,720 --> 00:47:45,480
Tap the basket to order.

589
00:47:46,240 --> 00:47:47,560
Awesome.

590
00:47:47,640 --> 00:47:49,040
You're too good at selling.

591
00:47:51,640 --> 00:47:53,840
Wow.

592
00:47:53,920 --> 00:47:59,120
Awesome? Is it a compliment or…

593
00:47:59,200 --> 00:48:00,960
This one. New quadriceps product.

594
00:48:01,040 --> 00:48:02,360
- No!
- Cordyceps product.

595
00:48:02,440 --> 00:48:03,800
- No!
- That's already correct.

596
00:48:03,880 --> 00:48:07,240
The emperor of tonics.

597
00:48:07,320 --> 00:48:10,280
This one will wake your warhorse up.

598
00:48:12,040 --> 00:48:14,840
<i>Thump, thump, all night long.</i>

599
00:48:14,920 --> 00:48:16,440
Special just for you, Mr. Trai.

600
00:48:16,520 --> 00:48:20,120
<i>Buy one, get one free!</i>

601
00:48:20,200 --> 00:48:22,360
Tap to order now,

602
00:48:22,440 --> 00:48:25,440
so you'll be lively day and night.

603
00:48:30,280 --> 00:48:33,160
What kind of lunatic is this?
She's way too good at selling.

604
00:48:35,120 --> 00:48:36,200
Crazy.

605
00:48:38,080 --> 00:48:40,680
So you had him watch
a live selling broadcast?

606
00:48:40,760 --> 00:48:41,760
Yeah.

607
00:48:42,440 --> 00:48:44,680
He's been waiting for Pakbung all day,
didn't you see?

608
00:48:45,560 --> 00:48:46,640
No, I didn't.

609
00:48:47,920 --> 00:48:50,120
Hey. Then look.

610
00:48:51,120 --> 00:48:53,400
Have you ever seen him smile like that?

611
00:48:54,200 --> 00:48:55,040
Look.

612
00:48:57,800 --> 00:48:59,120
You're right.

613
00:49:19,960 --> 00:49:20,800
Watch out.

614
00:49:21,320 --> 00:49:23,040
Your head. Slowly, slowly.

615
00:49:25,120 --> 00:49:26,160
There. Come on

616
00:49:26,880 --> 00:49:28,600
I'm covering your head.

617
00:49:29,200 --> 00:49:30,840
You okay?

618
00:49:30,920 --> 00:49:32,600
Yeah, Dad.

619
00:49:33,200 --> 00:49:35,000
- Let's go.
- Okay.

620
00:49:42,360 --> 00:49:44,040
What's wrong? A headache?

621
00:49:44,120 --> 00:49:45,480
You have a headache, right?

622
00:49:46,960 --> 00:49:48,600
I'm okay, Dad.

623
00:49:48,680 --> 00:49:49,680
Why?

624
00:49:51,280 --> 00:49:53,520
I carried you since you were little.

625
00:49:53,600 --> 00:49:55,440
I was also the one who taught you to walk.

626
00:49:56,240 --> 00:49:57,880
But I'm not a kid anymore, Dad.

627
00:49:57,960 --> 00:50:00,800
And my head hurts, not my legs.
Why are you holding me like this?

628
00:50:02,440 --> 00:50:04,080
Can't I take care of you for once?

629
00:50:07,200 --> 00:50:09,600
Fine, suit yourself.

630
00:50:09,680 --> 00:50:10,920
Let's go inside.

631
00:50:17,520 --> 00:50:18,920
Just a bit is fine.

632
00:50:19,880 --> 00:50:21,200
Am I little enough for you?

633
00:50:24,480 --> 00:50:26,760
Let's go, Dad. Let's go.

634
00:50:28,160 --> 00:50:29,680
You little puppy.

635
00:50:32,320 --> 00:50:34,560
So who's holding who now?

636
00:50:35,520 --> 00:50:36,600
Slowly.

637
00:50:43,600 --> 00:50:45,520
He went home and didn't even tell me.

638
00:50:46,160 --> 00:50:47,000
Such a waste of time.

639
00:50:47,600 --> 00:50:50,040
Then go visit him at his house.

640
00:50:51,000 --> 00:50:53,120
No. Waste of gas.

641
00:50:53,200 --> 00:50:54,920
And I've got work after this too.

642
00:50:56,360 --> 00:50:58,160
Hey, Bung.

643
00:50:58,240 --> 00:50:59,800
I have class too.

644
00:51:01,000 --> 00:51:03,760
Oh? Then go to class.

645
00:51:08,240 --> 00:51:10,240
Stop drinking your bubble tea.

646
00:51:10,320 --> 00:51:11,320
Go to class now.

647
00:51:11,400 --> 00:51:12,880
Fine, I'm going.

648
00:51:15,320 --> 00:51:16,600
- What now?
- Bung.

649
00:51:16,680 --> 00:51:19,960
I'm coming home tonight.
Wait for me, okay? Got it?

650
00:51:20,040 --> 00:51:23,280
- Yeah, go to class.
- Yeah, yeah.

651
00:51:37,760 --> 00:51:39,720
Nice. Two cups for me.

652
00:51:56,080 --> 00:51:57,080
Still here?

653
00:51:57,800 --> 00:51:59,280
I told you to go to class…

654
00:52:02,800 --> 00:52:04,240
Oh. It's you?

655
00:52:10,320 --> 00:52:12,680
I went to your place this morning

656
00:52:12,760 --> 00:52:14,400
and saw you came here.

657
00:52:14,480 --> 00:52:16,360
So you were stalking me?

658
00:52:19,080 --> 00:52:20,800
I think someone like me

659
00:52:20,880 --> 00:52:23,360
wouldn't have anything you'd want.

660
00:52:30,160 --> 00:52:32,320
I bought what you wanted.

661
00:52:32,400 --> 00:52:36,240
Consider it payment
for the handkerchief that day.

662
00:52:38,680 --> 00:52:41,080
That handkerchief
was just some cheap market thing.

663
00:52:41,160 --> 00:52:43,240
It wasn't made of gold, you know.

664
00:52:43,320 --> 00:52:46,440
The value doesn't depend on the price.

665
00:52:47,040 --> 00:52:48,600
But your handkerchief

666
00:52:49,200 --> 00:52:50,640
turned my special day,

667
00:52:51,240 --> 00:52:52,800
a day that almost wasn't special,

668
00:52:52,880 --> 00:52:54,760
into something meaningful.

669
00:52:56,320 --> 00:52:58,080
That much?

670
00:53:05,280 --> 00:53:06,440
What if I don't take it?

671
00:53:08,360 --> 00:53:09,480
That's your right.

672
00:53:09,560 --> 00:53:12,040
But I think someone like you

673
00:53:12,120 --> 00:53:13,280
isn't stupid, Pakbung.

674
00:53:13,960 --> 00:53:16,840
- Then I have one question.
- Go ahead.

675
00:53:16,920 --> 00:53:19,080
Mr. Trai got shot at

676
00:53:20,200 --> 00:53:21,520
and almost got grilled alive.

677
00:53:22,160 --> 00:53:23,640
Was that your doing?

678
00:53:27,480 --> 00:53:28,360
Everyone

679
00:53:29,360 --> 00:53:31,080
thinks it was me.

680
00:53:32,760 --> 00:53:34,040
I didn't do it.

681
00:53:36,760 --> 00:53:39,160
Not too fast, not too slow.

682
00:53:39,240 --> 00:53:42,040
Normal pupils. According to science,

683
00:53:42,120 --> 00:53:43,960
that means you're telling the truth.

684
00:53:47,280 --> 00:53:49,280
Your pupils…

685
00:53:49,960 --> 00:53:51,160
are bright,

686
00:53:51,960 --> 00:53:52,920
pretty.

687
00:54:01,040 --> 00:54:02,480
You still suspicious of Rachen?

688
00:54:05,760 --> 00:54:07,000
I want to be, Dad.

689
00:54:08,880 --> 00:54:11,280
But there's no proof he's the attacker.

690
00:54:11,360 --> 00:54:13,920
And he hates me, not you.

691
00:54:15,160 --> 00:54:16,600
Why would he threaten you?

692
00:54:17,760 --> 00:54:18,880
Thank you.

693
00:54:23,120 --> 00:54:25,360
For not suspecting your favorite son?

694
00:54:30,840 --> 00:54:32,160
For coming back home.

695
00:54:34,760 --> 00:54:35,960
Thank you.

696
00:54:40,840 --> 00:54:43,400
How can someone change overnight, Dad?

697
00:54:45,240 --> 00:54:47,520
The other day, you kicked me out.

698
00:54:47,600 --> 00:54:49,080
Today, you're happy I'm back?

699
00:54:50,880 --> 00:54:52,720
Then let me ask you this.

700
00:54:53,320 --> 00:54:54,400
If that day,

701
00:54:56,480 --> 00:54:58,000
I might've been the one to die,

702
00:55:01,480 --> 00:55:02,560
would you have changed?

703
00:55:09,360 --> 00:55:11,040
Trai, you know,

704
00:55:13,040 --> 00:55:15,040
when I found out you could've died,

705
00:55:17,240 --> 00:55:18,480
I felt like…

706
00:55:23,120 --> 00:55:25,360
my whole world had nothing left.

707
00:55:29,040 --> 00:55:30,520
I didn't know what I'd live for.

708
00:55:41,840 --> 00:55:43,160
I'm worried about you, Son.

709
00:55:46,800 --> 00:55:48,160
I really am.

710
00:56:00,320 --> 00:56:01,760
Thanks for coming home.

711
00:56:05,120 --> 00:56:06,200
Get some rest.

712
00:56:08,840 --> 00:56:10,400
Okay.

713
00:56:15,240 --> 00:56:16,640
Hello, Rut.

714
00:56:17,440 --> 00:56:19,840
I'm done here.
Bring the car around and wait.

715
00:56:23,080 --> 00:56:24,280
Matching cases?

716
00:56:25,000 --> 00:56:26,480
What does he want?

717
00:56:35,720 --> 00:56:38,040
Latest model, maxed-out storage,

718
00:56:38,120 --> 00:56:39,880
costs almost 50,000.

719
00:56:40,480 --> 00:56:43,400
If I resell it and buy a cheaper one,

720
00:56:44,160 --> 00:56:45,760
I'd still have over 10,000 left,

721
00:56:46,280 --> 00:56:47,640
enough to make more money.

722
00:56:48,240 --> 00:56:50,960
Couldn't you at least
keep that to yourself? I heard every word.

723
00:56:51,680 --> 00:56:53,120
I meant for you to hear.

724
00:56:59,080 --> 00:57:01,000
Then I won't take the phone.

725
00:57:06,120 --> 00:57:07,440
Can I trade the handkerchief fee

726
00:57:07,960 --> 00:57:09,320
for something else?

727
00:57:10,960 --> 00:57:11,800
Say it.

728
00:57:13,080 --> 00:57:14,800
You're close
with Mrs. Mookmanee, aren't you?

729
00:57:16,440 --> 00:57:18,440
Mrs. Mookmanee sued Petch

730
00:57:19,160 --> 00:57:21,000
and got all his jobs canceled.

731
00:57:21,080 --> 00:57:24,480
So instead of the phone, I want a chance.

732
00:57:25,120 --> 00:57:26,680
Can you talk to Mrs. Mookmanee

733
00:57:26,760 --> 00:57:28,600
to give Petch his jobs back

734
00:57:29,240 --> 00:57:31,320
and withdraw the lawsuit?

735
00:57:34,800 --> 00:57:37,360
I think you should use this phone
to find other opportunities instead.

736
00:57:38,560 --> 00:57:41,320
Take it.
Sell it or do whatever you want with it.

737
00:57:42,560 --> 00:57:44,200
But don't get involved
with Mrs. Mookmanee again.

738
00:57:44,920 --> 00:57:46,200
That's my only advice.

739
00:57:52,280 --> 00:57:55,120
You have to live
to make up for your mistakes.

740
00:57:55,200 --> 00:57:58,440
A star still shines in the dark,

741
00:57:58,520 --> 00:58:00,880
so you have to be brave like it.

742
00:58:00,960 --> 00:58:02,880
Don't give up, Mr. Trai.

743
00:58:05,480 --> 00:58:06,520
Darin!

744
00:58:06,600 --> 00:58:07,960
What the hell is wrong with you?

745
00:58:08,040 --> 00:58:09,560
I'm your woman too.

746
00:58:09,640 --> 00:58:11,520
You got a new phone?

747
00:58:11,600 --> 00:58:12,880
Rachen bought this for you?

748
00:58:13,880 --> 00:58:17,240
If you want authority, then go work.

749
00:58:17,320 --> 00:58:20,880
<i>Get ready to serve Be Rich's</i>
<i>second-generation owner,</i>

750
00:58:20,960 --> 00:58:22,320
<i>Mr. Board Member.</i>

751
00:58:22,400 --> 00:58:26,280
<i>A business that looks down on customers,</i>
<i>doesn't love them, doesn't help them grow,</i>

752
00:58:26,360 --> 00:58:28,040
will never ever prosper.

753
00:58:28,120 --> 00:58:29,040
Trai!

754
00:58:29,120 --> 00:58:32,320
You want to show everyone
I raised a useless son like this?

755
00:58:32,400 --> 00:58:34,640
Stop seeing Trai. How much do you want?

756
00:58:34,720 --> 00:58:37,040
Will you pay by check or cash?

757
00:58:37,120 --> 00:58:38,880
<i>How much do you think</i>

758
00:58:38,960 --> 00:58:40,560
<i>your son is worth,</i>

759
00:58:40,640 --> 00:58:42,200
<i>Mr. Tritot?</i>

760
00:59:28,800 --> 00:59:32,200
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
